 16    def __init__(

 18        data_models_context: DataModelsContext,

 22    ):
 23        # SETUP
 24        self._data_models_context = data_models_context

 27
 28        # UNPACK DATA
 29        self._data_model = self._data_models_context.get_instance_of(self._type_class)
 30        self._filename = self._data_model.filename if self._data_model else "Unknown"
 31        self._dataframe = self._data_model.data_loader_model.df_data.copy() if self._data_model else pd.DataFrame({})

 43    def check_columns_in_models_dataframes(
 44        self,
 45        required_columns: Dict[str, List[str]],
 46        model_dataframes: Dict[str, pd.DataFrame],
 47    ) -> List[str]:
 48        """
 49        Check if required columns exist in the provided dataframes for different models.
 50        :param required_columns: A dictionary where keys are model names and values are lists of required column names.
 51        :param model_dataframes: A dictionary where keys are model names and values are their corresponding dataframes.
 52        :return: A list of error messages for missing columns.
 53        """
 54        errors = []
 55
 56        # Check if columns exist
 57        for model_name, columns in required_columns.items():
 58            dataframe = model_dataframes[model_name]
 59            if dataframe is not None:
 60                for column in columns:
 61                    exists_column, error_msg = self.column_exists(dataframe, model_name, column)
 62                    if not exists_column:
 63                        errors.append(error_msg)
 64
 65        return errors
 66

 68    def column_exists(self, dataframe, filename, column) -> Tuple[bool, str]:
 69
 70        # How use: To use this method, you can call it directly with the dataframe and column name.
 71        exists, msg_error_column = DataFrameProcessing.column_exists(dataframe, filename, column)
 72        return exists, msg_error_column
 73
 74    def _column_exists(self, column: str) -> Tuple[bool, str]:
 75        exists, msg_error_column = DataFrameProcessing.column_exists(self._dataframe, self._filename, column)
 76        return exists, msg_error_column

 78    def _column_exists_dataframe(self, dataframe, column: str) -> Tuple[bool, str]:
 79        exists, msg_error_column = DataFrameProcessing.column_exists(dataframe, self._filename, column)
 80        return exists, msg_error_column

 82    def _check_text_length(self, column: str, max_len: int) -> Tuple[List[str], List[str]]:
 83        """Helper function to validate text length in a column."""
 84        warnings = []
 85        __, warnings_text_length = DataFrameProcessing.check_dataframe_text_length(

 87            file_name=self._filename,
 88            column=column,
 89            max_length=max_len,

 91        warnings.extend(warnings_text_length)
 92        return [], warnings

102    def build_reports(self, validations):
103        for func, report_key in validations:
104            try:
105                errors, warnings = func()
106                if errors or warnings:
107                    self._report_list.extend(self.TITLES_INFO[report_key], errors=errors, warnings=warnings)
108                self._errors.extend(errors)
109                self._warnings.extend(warnings)
110            except Exception as e:
111                self._report_list.extend(
112                    self.TITLES_INFO[report_key],
113                    errors=[f"Exception validation in file during {func.__name__}: {str(e)}"],
114                    warnings=[],
115                )

 46    def validate_html_in_descriptions(self) -> Tuple[List[str], List[str]]:
 47        warnings = []
 48        column = SpDescription.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_SIMPLE_DESC.name
 49        exists_column, msg_error_column = self._column_exists(column)
 50        if not exists_column:
 51            return [msg_error_column], []
 52        for index, row in self._dataframe.iterrows():
 53            if re.search("<.*?>", str(row[column])):
 54                index = int(str(index))
 55                warnings.append(f"{self._filename}, linha {index + 2}: Coluna '{column}' no pode conter cdigo HTML.")
 56        return [], warnings
 57
 58    def validate_sequential_codes(self) -> Tuple[List[str], List[str]]:
 59        errors = []
 60
 61        # 0. Check if the column exists
 62        column = SpDescription.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_CODE.name
 63        exists_column, msg_error_column = self._column_exists(column)
 64        if not exists_column:
 65            return [msg_error_column], []
 66
 67        # Load the original codes and cleaned codes
 68        original_codes = pd.to_numeric(self._dataframe[column], errors="coerce")
 69        codes_cleaned = self._data_model.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_CODE
 70
 71        # 1. Check if the column has only integers
 72        if original_codes.size != codes_cleaned.size:
 73            errors.append(f"{self._filename}: A verificao foi abortada porque a coluna '{column}' contm valores no numricos.")
 74            return errors, []
 75
 76        # 2. Check if the first code is 1
 77        if codes_cleaned.at[0] != 1:
 78            errors.append(f"{self._filename}: A coluna '{column}' deve comear em 1.")
 79
 80        # 3. Check if the codes are sequential and starting from 1
 81        if not codes_cleaned.equals(pd.Series(range(1, len(codes_cleaned) + 1))):
 82            errors.append(f"{self._filename}: A coluna '{column}' deve conter valores inteiros e sequenciais (1, 2, 3, ...).")
 83
 84        return errors, []
 85
 86    def validate_unique_codes(self) -> Tuple[List[str], List[str]]:
 87        errors = []
 88        column = SpDescription.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_CODE.name
 89        exists_column, msg_error_column = self._column_exists(column)
 90        if not exists_column:
 91            return [msg_error_column], []
 92
 93        codes_cleaned = self._data_model.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_CODE
 94        duplicated_codes = codes_cleaned[codes_cleaned.duplicated()].tolist()
 95
 96        if duplicated_codes:
 97            errors.append(f"{self._filename}: A coluna '{column}' contm cdigos duplicados: {duplicated_codes}.")
 98
 99        return errors, []

101    def validate_text_capitalization(self) -> Tuple[List[str], List[str]]:
102        warnings = []
103        columns_to_check = [
104            SpDescription.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_SIMPLE_NAME.name,
105            SpDescription.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_COMPLETE_NAME.name,
106        ]
107
108        for column in columns_to_check:
109            exists_column, msg_error_column = self._column_exists(column)
110            if not exists_column:
111                warnings.append(msg_error_column)
112                continue
113
114            # Filter non-empty values
115            mask = self._dataframe[column].notna() & (self._dataframe[column] != "")
116            filtered_data = self._dataframe[mask]
117
118            if not filtered_data.empty:
119                # Process original text with all replacements
120                original_series = (
121                    filtered_data[column]
122                    .astype(str)
123                    .str.replace("  ", " (EXTRA_SPACE)")
124                    .str.replace("\r", "(CR)")
125                    .str.replace("\n", "(LF)")
126                    .str.replace("\x0d", "(CR)")
127                    .str.replace("\x0a", "(LF)")
128                )
129
130                # Process expected correct text with all replacements and capitalization
131                expected_series = (
132                    filtered_data[column]
133                    .astype(str)
134                    .str.replace("\r", "")
135                    .str.replace("\n", "")
136                    .str.replace("\x0d", "")
137                    .str.replace("\x0a", "")
138                    .str.strip()
139                    .apply(lambda x: capitalize_text_keep_acronyms(x.strip()))
140                )
141
142                # Find mismatches
143                mismatches_mask = original_series != expected_series
144                mismatches_indices = original_series[mismatches_mask].index
145
146                for idx in mismatches_indices:
147                    original_text = original_series.loc[idx]
148                    expected_text = expected_series.loc[idx]
149                    warnings.append(
150                        f"{self._filename}, linha {idx + 2}: Valor da coluna '{column}' fora do padro. Esperado: '{expected_text}'. Encontrado: '{original_text}'."
151                    )
152
153        return [], warnings
154
155    def validate_indicator_levels(self) -> Tuple[List[str], List[str]]:
156        errors = []
157        column = SpDescription.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_LEVEL.name
158        exists_column, msg_error_column = self._column_exists(column)
159        if not exists_column:
160            return [msg_error_column], []
161
162        for index, row in self._dataframe.iterrows():
163            level = row[column]
164            is_valid, __ = NumberFormattingProcessing.check_cell_integer(level, min_value=1)
165            if not is_valid:
166                line_updated = int(index) + 2
167                errors.append(
168                    f"{self._filename}, linha {line_updated}: O nvel do indicador na coluna '{column}' deve ser um nmero inteiro maior que 0."
169                )
170        return errors, []
171
172    def validate_punctuation(self) -> Tuple[List[str], List[str]]:
173        warnings = []
174        columns_dont_punctuation = [
175            SpDescription.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_SIMPLE_NAME.name,
176            SpDescription.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_COMPLETE_NAME.name,
177        ]
178        columns_must_end_with_dot = [
179            SpDescription.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_SIMPLE_DESC.name,
180            SpDescription.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_COMPLETE_DESC.name,
181        ]
182
183        for column in list(columns_dont_punctuation + columns_must_end_with_dot):
184            exists_column, msg_error_column = self._column_exists(column)
185            if not exists_column:
186                warnings.append(msg_error_column)
187
188        _, punctuation_warnings = CharacterProcessing.check_characters_punctuation_rules(
189            self._dataframe,
190            self._filename,
191            columns_dont_punctuation,
192            columns_must_end_with_dot,
193        )
194        warnings.extend(punctuation_warnings)
195        return [], warnings
196
197    def validate_empty_strings(self) -> Tuple[List[str], List[str]]:
198        errors = []
199
200        columns_to_check = [
201            SpDescription.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_SIMPLE_NAME.name,
202            SpDescription.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_COMPLETE_NAME.name,
203            SpDescription.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_SIMPLE_DESC.name,
204            SpDescription.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_COMPLETE_DESC.name,
205        ]
206        for column in columns_to_check:
207            exists_column, msg_error_column = self._column_exists(column)
208            if not exists_column:
209                errors.append(msg_error_column)
210                continue
211            empty_rows = self._dataframe[self._dataframe[column].isna() | (self._dataframe[column] == "")].index
212            if not empty_rows.empty:
213                for index in empty_rows:
214                    errors.append(f"{self._filename}, linha {index + 2}: Nenhum item da coluna '{column}' pode ser vazio.")
215        return errors, []

217    def validate_cr_lf_characters(self) -> Tuple[List[str], List[str]]:
218        warnings = []
219
220        columns_start_end = self._data_model.EXPECTED_COLUMNS
221        columns_anywhere = [
222            SpDescription.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_SIMPLE_NAME.name,
223            SpDescription.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_COMPLETE_NAME.name,
224        ]
225
226        # Create an ordered dictionary with the columns
227        columns_to_check = list(OrderedDict.fromkeys(columns_anywhere + columns_start_end).keys())
228
229        # Check if the columns exist
230        for column in columns_to_check:
231            exists_column, msg_error_column = self._column_exists(column)
232            if not exists_column:
233                warnings.append(msg_error_column)
234                continue
235
236        # Run the checks for CR/LF characters
237        __, all_warnings_cr_lf = CharacterProcessing.check_special_characters_cr_lf(
238            self._dataframe, self._filename, columns_start_end, columns_anywhere
239        )
240
241        warnings.extend(all_warnings_cr_lf)
242        return [], warnings

244    def validate_title_length(self) -> Tuple[List[str], List[str]]:
245        """Validate the length of titles."""
246        column = SpDescription.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_SIMPLE_NAME.name
247        max_len = SpDescription.CONSTANTS.MAX_TITLE_LENGTH
248        return self._check_text_length(column, max_len)

250    def validate_simple_description_length(self) -> Tuple[List[str], List[str]]:
251        """Validate the length of simple descriptions."""
252        column = SpDescription.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_SIMPLE_DESC.name
253        max_len = SpDescription.CONSTANTS.MAX_SIMPLE_DESC_LENGTH
254        return self._check_text_length(column, max_len)

259    def run(self) -> Tuple[List[str], List[str]]:
260        """Runs all content validations for SpDescription."""
261        validations = [
262            (self.validate_html_in_descriptions, NamesEnum.HTML_DESC.value),
263            (self.validate_sequential_codes, NamesEnum.SC.value),
264            (self.validate_unique_codes, NamesEnum.CO_UN.value),
265            (self.validate_text_capitalization, NamesEnum.INP.value),
266            (self.validate_indicator_levels, NamesEnum.IL.value),
267            (self.validate_punctuation, NamesEnum.MAND_PUNC_DESC.value),
268            (self.validate_empty_strings, NamesEnum.EF.value),
269            (self.validate_cr_lf_characters, NamesEnum.LB_DESC.value),
270            (self.validate_simple_description_length, NamesEnum.SIMP_DESC_N.value),
271        ]
272        if self._dataframe.empty:
273            self.set_not_executed(validations)
274            return self._errors, self._warnings
275
276        # Add title length validation if the flag is not set to skip it
277        if not self._data_models_context.data_args.data_action.no_warning_titles_length:
278            validations.append((self.validate_title_length, NamesEnum.TITLES_N.value))
279
280        # BUILD REPORTS
281        self.build_reports(validations)
282
283        return self._errors, self._warnings

def validate_sequential_codes(self) -> Tuple[List[str], List[str]]: 
58    def validate_sequential_codes(self) -> Tuple[List[str], List[str]]:
59        errors = []
60
61        # 0. Check if the column exists
62        column = SpDescription.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_CODE.name
63        exists_column, msg_error_column = self._column_exists(column)
64        if not exists_column:
65            return [msg_error_column], []
66
67        # Load the original codes and cleaned codes
68        original_codes = pd.to_numeric(self._dataframe[column], errors="coerce")
69        codes_cleaned = self._data_model.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_CODE
70
71        # 1. Check if the column has only integers
72        if original_codes.size != codes_cleaned.size:
73            errors.append(f"{self._filename}: A verificao foi abortada porque a coluna '{column}' contm valores no numricos.")
74            return errors, []
75
76        # 2. Check if the first code is 1
77        if codes_cleaned.at[0] != 1:
78            errors.append(f"{self._filename}: A coluna '{column}' deve comear em 1.")
79
80        # 3. Check if the codes are sequential and starting from 1
81        if not codes_cleaned.equals(pd.Series(range(1, len(codes_cleaned) + 1))):
82            errors.append(f"{self._filename}: A coluna '{column}' deve conter valores inteiros e sequenciais (1, 2, 3, ...).")
83
84        return errors, []

def validate_text_capitalization(self) -> Tuple[List[str], List[str]]: 
101    def validate_text_capitalization(self) -> Tuple[List[str], List[str]]:
102        warnings = []
103        columns_to_check = [
104            SpDescription.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_SIMPLE_NAME.name,
105            SpDescription.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_COMPLETE_NAME.name,
106        ]
107
108        for column in columns_to_check:
109            exists_column, msg_error_column = self._column_exists(column)
110            if not exists_column:
111                warnings.append(msg_error_column)
112                continue
113
114            # Filter non-empty values
115            mask = self._dataframe[column].notna() & (self._dataframe[column] != "")
116            filtered_data = self._dataframe[mask]
117
118            if not filtered_data.empty:
119                # Process original text with all replacements
120                original_series = (
121                    filtered_data[column]
122                    .astype(str)
123                    .str.replace("  ", " (EXTRA_SPACE)")
124                    .str.replace("\r", "(CR)")
125                    .str.replace("\n", "(LF)")
126                    .str.replace("\x0d", "(CR)")
127                    .str.replace("\x0a", "(LF)")
128                )
129
130                # Process expected correct text with all replacements and capitalization
131                expected_series = (
132                    filtered_data[column]
133                    .astype(str)
134                    .str.replace("\r", "")
135                    .str.replace("\n", "")
136                    .str.replace("\x0d", "")
137                    .str.replace("\x0a", "")
138                    .str.strip()
139                    .apply(lambda x: capitalize_text_keep_acronyms(x.strip()))
140                )
141
142                # Find mismatches
143                mismatches_mask = original_series != expected_series
144                mismatches_indices = original_series[mismatches_mask].index
145
146                for idx in mismatches_indices:
147                    original_text = original_series.loc[idx]
148                    expected_text = expected_series.loc[idx]
149                    warnings.append(
150                        f"{self._filename}, linha {idx + 2}: Valor da coluna '{column}' fora do padro. Esperado: '{expected_text}'. Encontrado: '{original_text}'."
151                    )
152
153        return [], warnings

 85    def validate_relation_indicators_in_values(self) -> Tuple[List[str], List[str]]:
 86        """
 87        Validate indicator relationships between values and descriptions.
 88
 89        Returns:
 90            Tuple of (errors, warnings) lists
 91        """
 92        errors, warnings = [], []
 93
 94        if self.model_dataframes[self.sp_name_description].empty:
 95            return errors, warnings
 96
 97        errors = self.check_columns_in_models_dataframes(
 98            required_columns={
 99                self.sp_name_description: self.global_required_columns[self.sp_name_description],
100                self.sp_name_scenario: self.global_required_columns[self.sp_name_scenario],
101            },
102            model_dataframes=self.model_dataframes,
103        )
104        if errors:
105            return errors, warnings
106
107        code_column_name = SpDescription.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_CODE.name
108        level_column_name = SpDescription.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_LEVEL.name
109        scenario_column_name = SpDescription.DynamicColumn.COLUMN_SCENARIO.name
110
111        # Prepare cleaned dataframes
112        # No-need to clean the values dataframe
113        df_values = self.model_dataframes[self.sp_name_value].copy()
114        # Need to clean the description and temporal reference dataframes
115        df_description, _ = DataCleaningProcessing.clean_dataframe_integers(
116            self.model_dataframes[self.sp_name_description],
117            self.sp_name_description,
118            [code_column_name],
119        )
120
121        level_one_codes = df_description[df_description[level_column_name] == "1"][code_column_name].astype(str).tolist()
122
123        # Process value columns
124        value_columns = df_values.columns.tolist()
125        columns_to_ignore = self.global_required_columns[self.sp_name_value] + level_one_codes
126
127        valid_value_codes, invalid_columns = CollectionsProcessing.extract_numeric_ids_and_unmatched_strings_from_list(
128            value_columns, columns_to_ignore, self.list_scenarios
129        )
130
131        # Filter out columns containing ':'
132        processed_invalid_columns = sorted({col for col in invalid_columns if ":" not in col})
133
134        if processed_invalid_columns:
135            errors.append(f"{self.model_sp_value.filename}: Colunas invlidas: {processed_invalid_columns}.")
136
137        # Get filtered description codes using generic function
138        # Remove level 1 indicators
139        filtered_description_df = df_description[df_description[level_column_name] != "1"].copy()
140
141        # Remove level 2 indicators with scenario 0 if scenario column exists
142        if self.exists_scenario and scenario_column_name in filtered_description_df.columns:
143            filtered_description_df = filtered_description_df[
144                ~((filtered_description_df[level_column_name] == "2") & (filtered_description_df[scenario_column_name] == "0"))
145            ]
146
147        # Extract valid description codes
148        valid_description_codes, _ = CollectionsProcessing.extract_numeric_integer_ids_from_list(
149            id_values_list=set(filtered_description_df[code_column_name].astype(str))
150        )
151
152        # Compare codes between description and values
153        comparison_errors = CollectionsProcessing.find_differences_in_two_set_with_message(
154            first_set=valid_description_codes,
155            label_1=self.model_sp_description.filename,
156            second_set=valid_value_codes,
157            label_2=self.model_sp_value.filename,
158        )
159        errors.extend(comparison_errors)
160
161        return errors, warnings
162
163    def validate_value_combination_relation(self) -> Tuple[List[str], List[str]]:
164        """
165        Validate value combination relations between indicators and their expected columns.
166
167        This function ensures that each indicator has the correct combination of columns
168        in the values dataframe based on its level and scenario configuration.
169        """
170        errors, warnings = [], []
171
172        if self.model_dataframes[self.sp_name_description].empty or self.model_dataframes[self.sp_name_temporal_reference].empty:
173            return errors, warnings
174
175        code_column_name = SpDescription.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_CODE.name
176        level_column_name = SpDescription.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_LEVEL.name
177        scenario_column_name = SpDescription.DynamicColumn.COLUMN_SCENARIO.name
178        symbol_column_name = SpTemporalReference.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_SYMBOL.name
179
180        local_required_columns = self.global_required_columns.copy()
181        if self.exists_scenario:
182            local_required_columns[self.sp_name_description].append(scenario_column_name)
183
184        errors = self.check_columns_in_models_dataframes(
185            required_columns=local_required_columns,
186            model_dataframes=self.model_dataframes,
187        )
188        if errors:
189            return errors, warnings
190
191        # Prepare cleaned dataframes
192        # No-need to clean the values dataframe
193        df_values = self.model_dataframes[self.sp_name_value].copy()
194
195        # Need to clean the description and temporal reference dataframes
196        df_description, _ = DataCleaningProcessing.clean_dataframe_integers(
197            self.model_dataframes[self.sp_name_description],
198            self.sp_name_description,
199            local_required_columns[self.sp_name_description],
200        )
201        df_temporal_reference, _ = DataCleaningProcessing.clean_dataframe_integers(
202            self.model_dataframes[self.sp_name_temporal_reference],
203            self.sp_name_temporal_reference,
204            local_required_columns[self.sp_name_temporal_reference],
205        )
206
207        # Get temporal symbols once (sorted for consistency)
208        temporal_symbols = sorted(df_temporal_reference[symbol_column_name].unique())
209        first_year = temporal_symbols[0]
210        sp_value_columns = set(df_values.columns)
211
212        # Process each indicator efficiently
213        for _, row in df_description.iterrows():
214            code = str(row[code_column_name])
215            level = int(row[level_column_name])
216            scenario = int(row[scenario_column_name]) if self.exists_scenario else 0
217
218            # Generate expected combinations based on level and scenario
219            expected_combinations = []
220            if level >= 2:
221                if scenario == 0:
222                    expected_combinations = [f"{code}-{first_year}"]
223                elif scenario == 1:
224                    expected_combinations = CombinationsProcessing.generate_combinations(code, first_year, temporal_symbols, self.list_scenarios)
225
226            # Validate required combinations exist
227            for combination in expected_combinations:
228                if combination not in sp_value_columns:
229                    # Skip validation for level 2 with scenario 0 (special case)
230                    if level == 2 and scenario == 0:
231                        continue
232                    errors.append(f"{self.model_sp_value.filename}: A coluna '{combination}'  obrigatria.")
233
234            # Find actual combinations for this code
235            actual_combinations = [col for col in sp_value_columns if col.startswith(f"{code}-")]
236
237            # Check for extra combinations
238            has_extra_error, extra_columns = CombinationsProcessing.find_extra_combinations(expected_combinations, actual_combinations)
239            if has_extra_error:
240                for extra_column in extra_columns:
241                    if level == 1:
242                        errors.append(f"{self.model_sp_value.filename}: A coluna '{extra_column}'  desnecessria para o indicador de nvel 1.")
243                    else:
244                        errors.append(f"{self.model_sp_value.filename}: A coluna '{extra_column}'  desnecessria.")
245
246        return errors, warnings
247
248    def validate_unavailable_codes_values(self) -> Tuple[List[str], List[str]]:
249        """
250        Validate unavailable and invalid values in the data.
251
252        Checks for:
253        1. Invalid numeric values (not numbers and not "DI")
254        2. Values with more than 2 decimal places
255
256        Returns:
257            Tuple of (errors, warnings) lists
258        """
259        errors, warnings = [], []
260
261        errors = self.check_columns_in_models_dataframes(
262            required_columns={self.sp_name_scenario: (self.global_required_columns[self.sp_name_scenario] if self.exists_scenario else [])},
263            model_dataframes=self.model_dataframes,
264        )
265
266        if errors:
267            return errors, warnings
268
269        id_column_name = SpValue.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_ID.name
270
271        # Prepare dataframe for validation using generic function
272        df_values = self.model_dataframes[self.sp_name_value].copy()
273        if id_column_name in df_values.columns:
274            df_values = df_values.drop(columns=[id_column_name])
275
276        # Get valid columns that match ID patterns
277        valid_columns, _ = CollectionsProcessing.categorize_strings_by_id_pattern_from_list(df_values.columns, self.list_scenarios)
278
279        # Validate data values in columns using generic function
280        validation_errors, validation_warnings = ValueProcessing.validate_data_values_in_columns(
281            df_values, valid_columns, self.model_sp_value.filename
282        )
283
284        errors.extend(validation_errors)
285        warnings.extend(validation_warnings)
286
287        return errors, warnings
288
289    def run(self) -> Tuple[List[str], List[str]]:
290        """Runs all content validations for SpValue."""
291
292        validations = [
293            (self.validate_relation_indicators_in_values, NamesEnum.IR.value),
294            (self.validate_value_combination_relation, NamesEnum.VAL_COMB.value),
295            (self.validate_unavailable_codes_values, NamesEnum.UNAV_INV.value),
296        ]
297        if self._dataframe.empty:
298            self.set_not_executed(validations)
299            return self._errors, self._warnings
300
301        # BUILD REPORTS
302        self.build_reports(validations)
303
304        return self._errors, self._warnings

243                    else:
244                        errors.append(f"{self.model_sp_value.filename}: A coluna '{extra_column}'  desnecessria.")

109    def validate_hierarchy_with_tree(self) -> Tuple[List[str], List[str]]:
110        """
111        Validate tree composition structure and detect cycles.
112
113        Returns:
114            Tuple containing (errors, warnings) lists
115        """
116        errors: List[str] = []
117        warnings: List[str] = []
118
119        # Check required columns exist
120        column_errors = self.check_columns_in_models_dataframes(self.global_required_columns, self.model_dataframes)
121        if column_errors:
122            return column_errors, warnings
123
124        # Create working copies and clean data
125        df_composition = self.model_dataframes[self.sp_name_composition].copy()
126        df_description = self.model_dataframes[self.sp_name_description].copy()
127
128        # Clean integer columns: df_composition
129        df_composition, _ = DataCleaningProcessing.clean_dataframe_integers(
130            df=df_composition,
131            file_name=self.sp_name_composition,
132            columns_to_clean=[self.column_name_parent],
133            min_value=0,
134        )
135        df_composition, _ = DataCleaningProcessing.clean_dataframe_integers(
136            df=df_composition,
137            file_name=self.sp_name_composition,
138            columns_to_clean=[self.column_name_child],
139            min_value=1,
140        )
141
142        # Clean integer columns: df_description
143        df_description, _ = DataCleaningProcessing.clean_dataframe_integers(
144            df=df_description,
145            file_name=self.sp_name_description,
146            columns_to_clean=[self.column_name_code, self.column_name_level],
147            min_value=1,
148        )
149
150        # Add root node if not present
151        if not (df_description[self.column_name_code] == 0).any():
152            root_row = pd.DataFrame(
153                [len(self.model_sp_description.EXPECTED_COLUMNS) * [0]],
154                columns=self.model_sp_description.EXPECTED_COLUMNS,
155            )
156            df_description = pd.concat([df_description, root_row], ignore_index=True)
157
158        # Build tree and check for cycles
159        tree = TreeProcessing.create_tree_structure(df_composition, self.column_name_parent, self.column_name_child)
160
161        cycle_found, cycle = TreeProcessing.detect_tree_cycles(tree)
162        if cycle_found:
163            errors.append(f"{self.sp_name_composition}: Ciclo encontrado: [{' -> '.join(cycle)}].")
164
165        # Validate level composition
166        level_errors = TreeProcessing.validate_level_hierarchy(
167            df_composition,
168            df_description,
169            self.column_name_code,
170            self.column_name_level,
171            self.column_name_parent,
172            self.column_name_child,
173        )
174
175        errors.extend(self._format_level_errors(level_errors, df_composition, df_description))
176
177        return errors, warnings

179    def validate_tree_levels_children(self) -> Tuple[List[str], List[str]]:
180        """
181        Validate that all children of the same parent have the same level.
182
183        Returns:
184            Tuple containing (errors, warnings) lists
185        """
186        errors: List[str] = []
187        warnings: List[str] = []
188
189        # Check required columns exist
190        column_errors = self.check_columns_in_models_dataframes(self.global_required_columns, self.model_dataframes)
191        if column_errors:
192            return column_errors, warnings
193
194        df_composition = self.model_dataframes[self.sp_name_composition].copy()
195        df_description = self.model_dataframes[self.sp_name_description].copy()
196
197        # Create level mapping
198        levels = {row[self.column_name_code]: row[self.column_name_level] for _, row in df_description.iterrows()}
199
200        # Group by parent and validate children levels
201        parent_groups = df_composition.groupby(self.column_name_parent)
202        for parent, group in parent_groups:
203            if parent not in levels:
204                errors.append(f"{self.sp_name_composition}: Cdigo pai {parent} no encontrado na descrio.")
205                continue
206
207            children_info: List[Tuple[Any, Any]] = []
208
209            for _, row in group.iterrows():
210                child = row[self.column_name_child]
211                if child not in levels:
212                    errors.append(f"{self.sp_name_composition}: Cdigo filho {child} no encontrado na descrio.")
213                    continue
214                child_level = levels[child]
215                children_info.append((child, child_level))
216
217            if children_info and len({level for _, level in children_info}) > 1:
218                error_children = ", ".join([f"indicador {child} possui nvel '{level}'" for child, level in children_info])
219                errors.append(f"{self.sp_name_description}: Indicadores filhos do pai {parent} " f"no esto no mesmo nvel: [{error_children}].")
220
221        return errors, warnings
222
223    def _format_level_errors(
224        self,
225        level_errors: List[Tuple[Any, Any]],
226        df_composition: pd.DataFrame,
227        df_description: pd.DataFrame,
228    ) -> List[str]:
229        """
230        Format level composition errors with proper line numbers and descriptions.
231
232        Args:
233            level_errors: List of (parent, child) error tuples
234            df_composition: Composition dataframe
235            df_description: Description dataframe
236
237        Returns:
238            List of formatted error messages
239        """
240        formatted_errors: List[str] = []
241
242        for parent, child in level_errors:
243            if parent is not None and child is not None:
244                # Find the row with this relationship
245                matching_rows = df_composition[
246                    (df_composition[self.column_name_parent] == int(parent)) & (df_composition[self.column_name_child] == int(child))
247                ]
248
249                if not matching_rows.empty:
250                    row_index = matching_rows.index[0]
251                    line_number = row_index + 2
252
253                    parent_level = df_description[df_description[self.column_name_code] == int(parent)][self.column_name_level].values[0]
254
255                    child_level = df_description[df_description[self.column_name_code] == int(child)][self.column_name_level].values[0]
256
257                    formatted_errors.append(
258                        f"{self.sp_name_composition}, linha {line_number}: "
259                        f"O indicador {parent} (nvel {parent_level}) no pode ser pai "
260                        f"do indicador {child} (nvel {child_level}). "
261                        f"Atualize os nveis no arquivo de descrio."
262                    )
263
264        return formatted_errors

267        """
268        Execute all tree validation checks.

272        """

274            (self.validate_hierarchy_with_tree, NamesEnum.TH.value),
275            (self.validate_tree_levels_children, NamesEnum.CHILD_LVL.value),

277
278        if self.model_sp_composition.data_loader_model.df_data.empty or self.model_sp_description.data_loader_model.df_data.empty:
279            self.set_not_executed(validations)
280            return self._errors, self._warnings
281
282        self.build_reports(validations)
283
284        return self._errors, self._warnings

159        tree = TreeProcessing.create_tree_structure(df_composition, self.column_name_parent, self.column_name_child)
160
161        cycle_found, cycle = TreeProcessing.detect_tree_cycles(tree)
162        if cycle_found:
163            errors.append(f"{self.sp_name_composition}: Ciclo encontrado: [{' -> '.join(cycle)}].")
164
165        # Validate level composition
166        level_errors = TreeProcessing.validate_level_hierarchy(
167            df_composition,
168            df_description,
169            self.column_name_code,
170            self.column_name_level,
171            self.column_name_parent,
172            self.column_name_child,
173        )
174
175        errors.extend(self._format_level_errors(level_errors, df_composition, df_description))
176
177        return errors, warnings

def validate_tree_levels_children(self) -> Tuple[List[str], List[str]]: 
179    def validate_tree_levels_children(self) -> Tuple[List[str], List[str]]:
180        """
181        Validate that all children of the same parent have the same level.
182
183        Returns:
184            Tuple containing (errors, warnings) lists
185        """
186        errors: List[str] = []
187        warnings: List[str] = []
188
189        # Check required columns exist
190        column_errors = self.check_columns_in_models_dataframes(self.global_required_columns, self.model_dataframes)
191        if column_errors:
192            return column_errors, warnings
193
194        df_composition = self.model_dataframes[self.sp_name_composition].copy()
195        df_description = self.model_dataframes[self.sp_name_description].copy()
196
197        # Create level mapping
198        levels = {row[self.column_name_code]: row[self.column_name_level] for _, row in df_description.iterrows()}
199
200        # Group by parent and validate children levels
201        parent_groups = df_composition.groupby(self.column_name_parent)
202        for parent, group in parent_groups:
203            if parent not in levels:
204                errors.append(f"{self.sp_name_composition}: Cdigo pai {parent} no encontrado na descrio.")
205                continue
206
207            children_info: List[Tuple[Any, Any]] = []
208
209            for _, row in group.iterrows():
210                child = row[self.column_name_child]
211                if child not in levels:
212                    errors.append(f"{self.sp_name_composition}: Cdigo filho {child} no encontrado na descrio.")
213                    continue
214                child_level = levels[child]
215                children_info.append((child, child_level))
216
217            if children_info and len({level for _, level in children_info}) > 1:
218                error_children = ", ".join([f"indicador {child} possui nvel '{level}'" for child, level in children_info])
219                errors.append(f"{self.sp_name_description}: Indicadores filhos do pai {parent} " f"no esto no mesmo nvel: [{error_children}].")
220
221        return errors, warnings

284        if grafos_desconectados:

314                plural_column_one=column_plural_simple_name,
315                plural_column_two=column_plural_complete_name,
316            )
317            # Add prefix to warnings
318            warnings_i = [f"{self.sp_name_description}: {warning}" for warning in warnings_i]
319
320            # Add to main warnings list

122    def _check_sum_equals_one(self, subdatasets: Dict[str, DataFrame], sp_df_values: DataFrame, value_di: Any) -> Tuple[List[str], List[str]]:
123        """Orchestrates validation of sum equals one for all subdatasets."""
124        all_errors = []
125        all_warnings = []
126
127        global_has_excessive_decimals = False
128        global_count_excessive = 0
129        global_first_line_excessive = 0
130
131        precision = self._data_models_context.config.PRECISION_DECIMAL_PLACE_TRUNCATE
132
133        for parent_id, subdataset in subdatasets.items():
134            df_data = subdataset.iloc[:, 1:].copy()
135            ids = subdataset.iloc[:, 0]
136
137            # Step 1: Validate numeric format
138            is_di = df_data == value_di
139            df_data, format_errors = ProportionalityProcessing.validate_numeric_format(
140                df_data, is_di, value_di, parent_id, self.sp_name_proportionality
141            )
142            all_errors.extend(format_errors)
143
144            # Step 2: Check excessive decimals
145            has_excess, count_excess, first_line = ProportionalityProcessing.check_excessive_decimals(df_data, value_di, precision)
146
147            if has_excess:
148                if not global_has_excessive_decimals:
149                    global_first_line_excessive = first_line
150                global_has_excessive_decimals = True
151                global_count_excessive += count_excess
152
153            # Step 3: Convert to Decimal and sum
154            row_sums = ProportionalityProcessing.convert_to_decimal_and_sum(df_data, value_di, precision)
155
156            # Step 4: Validate zero sum rows
157            zero_errors = ProportionalityProcessing.validate_zero_sum_rows(
158                row_sums,
159                ids,
160                df_data,
161                sp_df_values,
162                self.column_name_id,
163                value_di,
164                self.sp_name_proportionality,
165                self.sp_name_value,
166            )
167            all_errors.extend(zero_errors)
168
169            # Step 5: Validate sum tolerance
170            tolerance_errors, tolerance_warnings = ProportionalityProcessing.validate_sum_tolerance(
171                row_sums,
172                parent_id,
173                self.sp_name_proportionality,
174                self._data_models_context.lm.current_language,
175            )
176            all_errors.extend(tolerance_errors)
177            all_warnings.extend(tolerance_warnings)
178
179        # Global warning for excessive decimals
180        if global_has_excessive_decimals:
181            text_existem = "Existem" if global_count_excessive > 1 else "Existe"
182            text_valores = "valores" if global_count_excessive > 1 else "valor"
183            all_warnings.append(
184                f"{self.sp_name_proportionality}, linha {global_first_line_excessive}: "
185                f"{text_existem} {global_count_excessive} {text_valores} com mais de 3 casas decimais, "
186                f"sero consideradas apenas as 3 primeiras casas decimais."
187            )
188
189        return all_errors, all_warnings

191    def validate_relation_indicators_in_proportionality(self) -> Tuple[List[str], List[str]]:
192        errors, warnings = [], []

194        if self.model_dataframes[self.sp_name_description].empty:

357    def validate_parent_child_relationships(self) -> Tuple[List[str], List[str]]:
358        errors, warnings = [], []
359        if self.model_dataframes[self.sp_name_composition].empty:
360            self.set_not_executed(
361                [

363                        self.validate_parent_child_relationships,
364                        NamesEnum.IND_VAL_PROP.value,
365                    )
366                ]
367            )
368            return errors, warnings

370        # Somente com dados de descricao e composicao (deve ser igual, apenas extrair)
371        local_required_columns = {
372            self.sp_name_proportionality: self.global_required_columns[self.sp_name_proportionality],
373            self.sp_name_composition: self.global_required_columns[self.sp_name_composition],
374        }
375
376        # Check required columns exist
377        column_errors = self.check_columns_in_models_dataframes(local_required_columns, self.model_dataframes)
378        if column_errors:
379            return column_errors, warnings
380
381        # Setup dataframes
382        df_composition = self.model_dataframes[self.sp_name_composition].copy()
383
384        # Build subdatasets
385        subdatasets = ProportionalityProcessing.build_subdatasets(self.model_dataframes[self.sp_name_proportionality], self.column_name_id)
386
387        # Filter composition to remove level 1 parents
388        df_composition = df_composition[df_composition[self.column_name_parent] != "1"]
389
390        dict_grouped_composition = {}
391        for __, row in df_composition.iterrows():
392            parent = row[self.column_name_parent]
393            child = row[self.column_name_child]
394
395            if parent not in dict_grouped_composition:
396                dict_grouped_composition[parent] = []
397
398            dict_grouped_composition[parent].append(child)
399
400        for parent_id, subdataset in subdatasets.items():
401
402            cleaned_parent_id = parent_id.split("-")[0]
403
404            if cleaned_parent_id not in dict_grouped_composition.keys():
405                if ":" not in parent_id:
406                    errors.append(
407                        f"{self.sp_name_proportionality}: O indicador pai '{cleaned_parent_id}' (em '{parent_id}') no est presente na coluna '{self.column_name_parent}' da planilha {self.sp_name_composition}."
408                    )
409                continue
410
411            children_codes = [col for col in subdataset.columns.tolist() if not col.lower().startswith(self.column_name_id)]
412            children_codes_cleaned = [filho.split("-")[0] for filho in children_codes]
413
414            dict_children_codes_cleaned = dict()
415            dict_children_codes_cleaned.setdefault(cleaned_parent_id, []).extend(children_codes_cleaned)
416
417            set_errors = {
418                f"{self.sp_name_proportionality}: O indicador '{filho}' (em '{filho_orig}') no  filho do indicador '{cleaned_parent_id}' (em '{parent_id}') conforme especificado em {self.sp_name_composition}."
419                for filho, filho_orig in zip(children_codes_cleaned, children_codes)
420                if filho not in dict_grouped_composition[cleaned_parent_id]
421            }
422            errors.extend(set_errors)
423
424            for child in dict_grouped_composition[cleaned_parent_id]:
425                if child not in dict_children_codes_cleaned[cleaned_parent_id]:
426                    code_pai_local = parent_id.split("-")[0]
427                    errors.append(
428                        f"{self.sp_name_proportionality}: Deve existir pelo menos uma relao do indicador filho '{child}' com o indicador pai '{code_pai_local}' (em '{parent_id}') conforme especificado em {self.sp_name_composition}."
429                    )
430
431        errors = sorted(set(errors))
432
433        return errors, warnings

467    def run(self) -> Tuple[List[str], List[str]]:
468        """Runs all content validations for SpProportionality."""
469
470        validations = [
471            (self.validate_relation_indicators_in_proportionality, NamesEnum.IR.value),
472            (self.validate_columns_repeated_indicators, NamesEnum.REP_IND_PROP.value),
473            (self.validate_relation_indicators_in_value_and_proportionality, NamesEnum.IND_VAL_PROP.value),
474            (self.validate_parent_child_relationships, NamesEnum.IR_PROP.value),
475            (self.validate_sum_properties_in_influencing_factors, NamesEnum.SUM_PROP.value),
476        ]
477        if self._dataframe.empty:
478            self.set_not_executed(validations)
479            return self._errors, self._warnings
480
481        # BUILD REPORTS
482        self.build_reports(validations)
483
484        return self._errors, self._warnings

390        dict_grouped_composition = {}
391        for __, row in df_composition.iterrows():
392            parent = row[self.column_name_parent]
393            child = row[self.column_name_child]
394
395            if parent not in dict_grouped_composition:
396                dict_grouped_composition[parent] = []
397
398            dict_grouped_composition[parent].append(child)
399
400        for parent_id, subdataset in subdatasets.items():
401
402            cleaned_parent_id = parent_id.split("-")[0]
403
404            if cleaned_parent_id not in dict_grouped_composition.keys():
405                if ":" not in parent_id:
406                    errors.append(
407                        f"{self.sp_name_proportionality}: O indicador pai '{cleaned_parent_id}' (em '{parent_id}') no est presente na coluna '{self.column_name_parent}' da planilha {self.sp_name_composition}."
408                    )
409                continue
410
411            children_codes = [col for col in subdataset.columns.tolist() if not col.lower().startswith(self.column_name_id)]
412            children_codes_cleaned = [filho.split("-")[0] for filho in children_codes]
413
414            dict_children_codes_cleaned = dict()
415            dict_children_codes_cleaned.setdefault(cleaned_parent_id, []).extend(children_codes_cleaned)
416
417            set_errors = {
418                f"{self.sp_name_proportionality}: O indicador '{filho}' (em '{filho_orig}') no  filho do indicador '{cleaned_parent_id}' (em '{parent_id}') conforme especificado em {self.sp_name_composition}."
419                for filho, filho_orig in zip(children_codes_cleaned, children_codes)
420                if filho not in dict_grouped_composition[cleaned_parent_id]
421            }
422            errors.extend(set_errors)
423
424            for child in dict_grouped_composition[cleaned_parent_id]:
425                if child not in dict_children_codes_cleaned[cleaned_parent_id]:
426                    code_pai_local = parent_id.split("-")[0]
427                    errors.append(
428                        f"{self.sp_name_proportionality}: Deve existir pelo menos uma relao do indicador filho '{child}' com o indicador pai '{code_pai_local}' (em '{parent_id}') conforme especificado em {self.sp_name_composition}."
429                    )
430
431        errors = sorted(set(errors))
432
433        return errors, warnings

447
448        # Somente com dados de descricao e composicao (deve ser igual, apenas extrair)

 92    def validate_relation_indicators_in_legend(self) -> Tuple[List[str], List[str]]:
 93        errors, warnings = [], []
 94
 95        if not self.model_sp_legend.is_sanity_check_passed:
 96            return errors, warnings
 97
 98        required_columns = {
 99            self.sp_name_description: [
100                SpDescription.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_CODE.name,
101                SpDescription.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_LEVEL.name,
102                SpDescription.DynamicColumn.COLUMN_LEGEND.name,
103            ]
104        }
105
106        for column in required_columns[self.sp_name_description]:
107            exists_column, msg_error = self.column_exists(
108                self.model_dataframes[self.sp_name_description],
109                self.sp_name_description,
110                column,
111            )
112            if not exists_column:
113                errors.append(msg_error)
114                break
115
116        if errors:
117            return errors, warnings
118
119        df_legend = self.model_dataframes[self.sp_name_legend].copy()
120        df_description = self.model_dataframes[self.sp_name_description].copy()
121
122        df_description_clean, __ = DataCleaningProcessing.clean_dataframe_integers(
123            df_description,
124            self.sp_name_description,
125            [SpDescription.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_CODE.name],
126            min_value=1,
127        )
128
129        df_description_clean[SpDescription.DynamicColumn.COLUMN_LEGEND.name] = pd.to_numeric(
130            df_description_clean[SpDescription.DynamicColumn.COLUMN_LEGEND.name],
131            errors="coerce",
132        )
133        df_description_clean[SpDescription.DynamicColumn.COLUMN_LEGEND.name] = df_description_clean[
134            SpDescription.DynamicColumn.COLUMN_LEGEND.name
135        ].astype("Int64")
136
137        # Remove all NaN values in column COLUMN_LEGEND
138        df_description_clean = df_description_clean.dropna(subset=[SpDescription.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_CODE.name])
139        df_legend = df_legend.dropna(subset=[SpLegend.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_CODE.name])
140
141        legends_id_in_description = (
142            df_description_clean[
143                (df_description_clean[SpDescription.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_LEVEL.name] != "1")
144                & (df_description_clean[SpDescription.DynamicColumn.COLUMN_LEGEND.name].notna())
145                & (
146                    pd.to_numeric(
147                        df_description_clean[SpDescription.DynamicColumn.COLUMN_LEGEND.name],
148                        errors="coerce",
149                    ).notna()
150                )
151            ][SpDescription.DynamicColumn.COLUMN_LEGEND.name]
152            .astype(str)
153            .tolist()
154        )  # DROP NA VALUES
155
156        legends_id_in_legend = df_legend[SpLegend.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_CODE.name].astype(str).unique().tolist()
157
158        set_one = set(legends_id_in_description)
159        set_two = set(legends_id_in_legend)
160
161        missing_in_b, missing_in_a = CollectionsProcessing.find_differences_in_two_set(
162            first_set=set_one,
163            second_set=set_two,
164        )
165
166        missing_in_b = {int(x) for x in missing_in_b if str(x).isdigit()}
167        missing_in_a = {int(x) for x in missing_in_a if str(x).isdigit()}
168
169        if missing_in_b:
170            errors.append(f"{self.sp_name_description}: Cdigos de legenda ausentes em {self.sp_name_legend}: {sorted(list(missing_in_b))}.")
171
172        if missing_in_a:
173            warnings.append(
174                f"{self.sp_name_legend}: Cdigos de legenda no referenciados em {self.sp_name_description}: {sorted(list(missing_in_a))}."
175            )
176
177        # 1. All codes that are level 1 - Cannot have legends: if they do, error
178
179        codes_indicators_level_one = (
180            df_description_clean[df_description_clean[SpDescription.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_LEVEL.name] == "1"][
181                SpDescription.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_CODE.name
182            ]
183            .astype(str)
184            .tolist()
185        )
186
187        legends_id_in_description_level_one = (
188            df_description_clean[
189                (df_description_clean[SpDescription.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_LEVEL.name] == "1")
190                & (df_description_clean[SpDescription.DynamicColumn.COLUMN_LEGEND.name].notna())
191            ][SpDescription.DynamicColumn.COLUMN_LEGEND.name]
192            .unique()
193            .astype(str)
194            .tolist()
195        )
196
197        if legends_id_in_description_level_one:
198            errors.append(
199                f"{self.sp_name_description}: Indicadores de nvel 1 no podem ter referncia de legenda. Cdigos com referncia em {self.sp_name_legend}: {sorted(list(codes_indicators_level_one))}."
200            )
201
202        # 3. All codes that are not level 1 and not level 2 - Must have a legend reference: if not, error
203        codes_indicators_other_levels = (

208            .astype(str)

210        )

224        missing_legends_other_levels = set_codes_other_levels - set_codes_with_legend

 21    """
 22    Validates the content of the SpScenario spreadsheet.

 28        report_list: ModelListReport,
 29        **kwargs: Dict[str, Any],
 30    ):
 31        super().__init__(
 32            data_models_context=data_models_context,
 33            report_list=report_list,
 34            type_class=SpDictionary,
 35            **kwargs,
 36        )
 37
 38        # Configure
 39        self.dictionary: SpDictionary | None = self._data_models_context.get_instance_of(SpDictionary)
 40        self.lang_dict_spell = self._data_models_context.data_args.data_file.locale
 41
 42        # From SpDictionary extract words to ignore
 43        self.list_words_user = self.dictionary.words_to_ignore
 44
 45        # My spellchecker
 46        self.spellchecker = SpellChecker(self.lang_dict_spell, self.list_words_user)
 47
 48        # Define column mappings for each model type
 49        self.model_columns_map: Dict[Type[Union[SpDescription, SpTemporalReference, SpScenario]], List[str]] = {
 50            SpDescription: [
 51                SpDescription.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_SIMPLE_NAME.name,
 52                SpDescription.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_COMPLETE_NAME.name,
 53                SpDescription.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_SIMPLE_DESC.name,
 54                SpDescription.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_COMPLETE_DESC.name,
 55            ],
 56            SpTemporalReference: [
 57                SpTemporalReference.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_DESCRIPTION.name,
 58            ],
 59            SpScenario: [
 60                SpScenario.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_NAME.name,
 61                SpScenario.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_DESCRIPTION.name,
 62            ],
 63        }
 64
 65        # Run pipeline
 66        self.run()
 67
 68    def validate_spellchecker(self, model_class: Type[Union[SpDescription, SpTemporalReference, SpScenario]]) -> Tuple[List[str], List[str]]:
 69        """
 70        Generic spellchecker validation method that works with any model class.
 71
 72        Args:
 73            model_class: The model class to validate (e.g., SpDescription, SpTemporalReference, SpScenario)
 74
 75        Returns:
 76            Tuple containing lists of errors and warnings
 77        """
 78        errors, warnings = [], []
 79
 80        # Configure local instances
 81        self._data_model = self._data_models_context.get_instance_of(model_class)
 82        self._dataframe = self._data_model.data_loader_model.df_data.copy()
 83        self._filename = self._data_model.filename
 84
 85        if self._dataframe.empty:
 86            return errors, warnings
 87
 88        # Get columns to check for this model
 89        columns_to_check = self.model_columns_map.get(model_class, [])
 90
 91        if not columns_to_check:
 92            # If no columns defined for this model, skip validation
 93            return errors, warnings
 94
 95        # Check if the columns exist
 96        for column in columns_to_check:
 97            exists_column, msg_error_column = self._column_exists(column)
 98            if not exists_column:
 99                warnings.append(msg_error_column)
100                continue
101
102        # Perform spellcheck
103        errors_spellchecker, warnings_spellchecker = self.spellchecker.check_spelling_text(
104            df=self._dataframe,
105            file_name=self._filename,
106            columns_sheets=columns_to_check,
107        )
108
109        errors.extend(sorted(errors_spellchecker))
110        warnings.extend(sorted(warnings_spellchecker))
111
112        return errors, warnings
113
114    def _prepare_statement(self):
115        if self.spellchecker.errors_dictionary:
116            self._errors.extend(self.spellchecker.errors_dictionary)
117
118    def run(self) -> Tuple[List[str], List[str]]:
119        """Runs all content validations for SpScenario."""
120
121        validations = []
122        if not self._data_models_context.data_args.data_action.no_spellchecker:
123            # Add validation for Description
124            validations.append(
125                (
126                    lambda: self.validate_spellchecker(SpDescription),
127                    NamesEnum.SPELL.value,
128                )
129            )
130
131            # Add validation for Temporal Reference
132            validations.append(
133                (
134                    lambda: self.validate_spellchecker(SpTemporalReference),
135                    NamesEnum.SPELL.value,
136                )
137            )
138
139            # Add validation for Scenario if scenarios exist
140            if self._data_model.scenarios_list:
141                validations.append(
142                    (
143                        lambda: self.validate_spellchecker(SpScenario),
144                        NamesEnum.SPELL.value,
145                    )
146                )
147
148        # BUILD REPORTS
149        self.build_reports(validations)
150
151        # Cleanup temporary files
152        self.spellchecker.clean_files_generated()
153
154        return self._errors, self._warnings

def validate_spellchecker( self, model_class: Type[Union[data_validate.models.SpDescription, data_validate.models.SpTemporalReference, data_validate.models.SpScenario]]) -> Tuple[List[str], List[str]]: 
 68    def validate_spellchecker(self, model_class: Type[Union[SpDescription, SpTemporalReference, SpScenario]]) -> Tuple[List[str], List[str]]:
 69        """
 70        Generic spellchecker validation method that works with any model class.
 71
 72        Args:
 73            model_class: The model class to validate (e.g., SpDescription, SpTemporalReference, SpScenario)
 74
 75        Returns:
 76            Tuple containing lists of errors and warnings
 77        """
 78        errors, warnings = [], []
 79
 80        # Configure local instances
 81        self._data_model = self._data_models_context.get_instance_of(model_class)
 82        self._dataframe = self._data_model.data_loader_model.df_data.copy()
 83        self._filename = self._data_model.filename
 84
 85        if self._dataframe.empty:
 86            return errors, warnings
 87
 88        # Get columns to check for this model
 89        columns_to_check = self.model_columns_map.get(model_class, [])
 90
 91        if not columns_to_check:
 92            # If no columns defined for this model, skip validation
 93            return errors, warnings
 94
 95        # Check if the columns exist
 96        for column in columns_to_check:
 97            exists_column, msg_error_column = self._column_exists(column)
 98            if not exists_column:
 99                warnings.append(msg_error_column)
100                continue
101
102        # Perform spellcheck
103        errors_spellchecker, warnings_spellchecker = self.spellchecker.check_spelling_text(
104            df=self._dataframe,
105            file_name=self._filename,
106            columns_sheets=columns_to_check,
107        )
108
109        errors.extend(sorted(errors_spellchecker))
110        warnings.extend(sorted(warnings_spellchecker))
111
112        return errors, warnings

 61    def check_empty_directory(self) -> tuple[bool, List[str]]:
 62        """
 63        Check if the input directory is empty.
 64
 65        Returns:
 66            bool: True if the directory is empty, False otherwise.
 67        """
 68        local_errors = []
 69        is_empty, message = self.context.fs_utils.check_directory_is_empty(self.context.data_args.data_file.input_folder)
 70        if is_empty:
 71            local_errors.append(
 72                self.context.lm.text(

 74                    dir_path=self.context.data_args.data_file.input_folder,
 75                )
 76            )
 77        return not local_errors, local_errors
 78
 79    def check_not_expected_files_in_folder_root(self) -> tuple[bool, List[str]]:
 80        """
 81        Check for unexpected folders or files in the input directory.
 82        """
 83        local_errors = []
 84        expected_files = self.context.config.EXPECTED_FILES
 85        optional_files = self.context.config.OPTIONAL_FILES
 86
 87        if len(self.dir_files) == 1:
 88            dir_path = os.path.join(self.context.data_args.data_file.input_folder, self.dir_files[0])
 89            is_dir, _ = self.context.fs_utils.check_directory_exists(dir_path)
 90            if is_dir:
 91                local_errors.append(self.context.lm.text("validator_structure_error_files_not_in_folder"))
 92                return not local_errors, local_errors
 93
 94        for file_name in self.dir_files:
 95            file_path = os.path.join(self.context.data_args.data_file.input_folder, file_name)
 96            is_file, _ = self.context.fs_utils.check_file_exists(file_path)
 97            if not is_file:
 98                local_errors.append(self.context.lm.text("validator_structure_error_unexpected_folder").format(file_name=file_name))
 99                continue
100
101            file_base, file_ext = os.path.splitext(file_name)
102            if file_base in expected_files and file_ext in expected_files[file_base]:
103                continue
104            if file_base in optional_files and file_ext in optional_files[file_base]:
105                continue
106
107            local_errors.append(self.context.lm.text("validator_structure_error_unexpected_file").format(file_name=file_name))
108
109        return not local_errors, local_errors
110
111    def check_expected_files_in_folder_root(self) -> tuple[bool, List[str]]:
112        """
113        Check if all expected files are present in the input directory.
114        """
115        local_errors = []
116        expected_files = self.context.config.EXPECTED_FILES
117
118        for file_base, extensions in expected_files.items():
119            file_found = False
120            for ext in extensions:
121                file_path = os.path.join(self.context.data_args.data_file.input_folder, f"{file_base}{ext}")
122                is_file, _ = self.context.fs_utils.check_file_exists(file_path)
123                if is_file:
124                    file_found = True
125                    break
126            if not file_found:
127                local_errors.append(self.context.lm.text("validator_structure_error_missing_file").format(file_base=file_base))
128        return not local_errors, local_errors
129
130    def check_ignored_files_in_folder_root(self) -> tuple[bool, List[str]]:
131        """
132        Check for files that will be ignored in the root folder.
133        Emit an error if both .xlsx and .csv files with the same name exist.
134        """
135        local_errors = []
136        file_groups = {}
137
138        for file_name in self.dir_files:
139            file_base, file_ext = os.path.splitext(file_name)
140            if file_ext in [".xlsx", ".csv"]:
141                if file_base not in file_groups:
142                    file_groups[file_base] = []
143                file_groups[file_base].append(file_ext)
144
145        for file_base, extensions in file_groups.items():
146            if ".xlsx" in extensions and ".csv" in extensions:
147                local_errors.append(self.context.lm.text("validator_structure_error_conflicting_files").format(file_base=file_base))
148
149        return not local_errors, local_errors
150
151    def validate_all_general_structure(self) -> Tuple[List[str], List[str]]:
152        """
153        Perform all validation checks on the input folder.
154
155        Returns:
156            List[str]: A list of validation errors.
157        """
158        all_errors = [
159            [self.check_empty_directory()],
160            [self.check_not_expected_files_in_folder_root()],
161            [self.check_expected_files_in_folder_root()],
162            [self.check_ignored_files_in_folder_root()],
163        ]
164        for check in all_errors:
165            is_valid, errors = check[0]
166            if not is_valid:
167                self.errors.extend(errors)
168
169        return self.errors, []
